<subSubSection id="C35C6510FFCFED045231D6DAA3575171" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF9369BFFCFED045231D6DAA3575171" blockId="21.[264,1325,284,1150]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCFED045231D6DAA69556BA" box="[312,414,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
: The apophysis of the style in the 
<typeStatus id="54FD8839FFCFED045041D6DAA4A656B9" box="[840,941,924,950]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paratype</typeStatus>
male is much longer and more slender and the aedeagal shaft is also slightly longer than in the 
<typeStatus id="54FD8839FFCFED0450FFD682A35656D1" box="[1014,1117,964,990]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
male. 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFCFED0457A7D682A22156D2" box="[1198,1322,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCFED0457A7D682A22156D2" box="[1198,1322,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the coloration of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFCFED0451C8D6AAA459510A" box="[705,850,1004,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCFED0451C8D6AAA459510A" box="[705,850,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Scaphotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is unique in having numerous long (almost twice as long as the subgenital plate) hairlike setae on the submarginal plate, to which the specific name alludes. It shares the basally fused paraphyses with 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFCFED04578CD17AA3F5515A" box="[1157,1278,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hussa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCFED04578CD17AA3F5515A" box="[1157,1278,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in colour and, male genital structure and is also a smaller species.
</paragraph>
